Class Complex

  • java.lang.Object
    • quantum.Complex

  • public class Complex
extends java.lang.Object
    The Complex class represents a complex number with a magnitude and a phase.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Complex

        public Complex(double r)
        Creates a complex number with a given real part, and no imaginary part. This number will have a phase of 0.
        Parameters:
        r - a double for the real part of a complex number

      • Complex

        public Complex(double r,
               double theta)
        Creates a complex number with a given magnitude and phase. The theta value will be changed such that it is within [0,2*Math.PI) and the r value is positive.
        Parameters:
        r - magnitude of the complex number to be created
        theta - phase of the complex number to be created
